The '''Braunwaldbahn''', '''Braunwald-Standseilbahn''' ('''BRSB'''), or '''Braunwald Funicular''', is a [[funicular railway]] in the [[canton of Glarus]], [[Switzerland]]. The line links [[Linthal Braunwaldbahn railway station|Linthal Braunwaldbahn station]], on the [[Swiss Federal Railways]]' [[Weesen-Linthal railway line|Weesen to Linthal line]], with the car-free resort of [[Braunwald, Glarus|Braunwald]] on the mountain above.<ref name=saw24>{{cite book | title = Eisenbahnatlas Schweiz | year = 2012 | publisher = Verlag Schweers+Wall GmbH | isbn=978-3-89494-130-7 | page = 24}}</ref>
The line was opened in 1907.<ref name=HDS>{{cite web | url = http://www.hls-dhs-dss.ch/textes/f/F760.php | title = Braunwald | language = French | work = [[Historical Dictionary of Switzerland]] | date = 2004-10-14 | accessdate = 2015-04-28}}</ref><ref name=bwcr>{{cite web | url = http://www.braunwald.ch/en/getting-here/standseilbahn | title = Braunwald - Cable Railway | publisher = Braunwald-Klausenpass Tourismus AG | accessdate = 2015-04-28}}</ref>
== Operation == The line is operated by the Braunwald-Standseilbahn AG and has the following parameters:<ref name=saw24/>
