{{Infobox Union |name= SSM |country= [[Republic of Macedonia]] |affiliation= [[ETUC]] (Observer status) |members= |full_name= Federation of Trade Unions of Macedonia |native_name= |image= |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Skopje]], Macedonia |people= |website=http://www.ssm.org.mk |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Federation of Trade Unions of Macedonia''' (Сојуз на синдикатите на Македонија, abbreviated as ССМ in Cyrillic text, transliterated as '''SSM''') is a [[national trade union center]] in the [[Republic of Macedonia]]. It is the successor to the official trade unions of the former [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavian]] era. The federation has 18 affiliated sectoral unions. Its president is Zivko Mitrevski.
The SSM is not affiliated at the international level, but holds observer status with the [[European Trade Union Confederation]].<ref>[http://www.etuc.org/a/83 ETUC, Observer Organisations]</ref>
