{{Infobox World's Fair | box_width = | class = Horticultural | category = | image = | image_width = | caption = | year = 1960 | name = Floriade 1960 | motto = | building = | area = | invent = | visitors = | organized = | cnt = | org = | biz = | country = Netherlands | city = [[Rotterdam]] | venue = Het Park | coord = | cand = | award = | open = {{start date|1960|03|25|df=y}} | close = {{start date|1960|09|25|df=y}} | prevexpo = | prevcity = | nextexpo = [[Hamburg 1963]] | nextcity = [[Hamburg]] | suppl = | prevsuppl = [[Interbau]] | prevsupcity = [[Berlin]] | nextsuppl = [[Expo 61]] | nextsupcity =[[Turin]] | prevunho = [[Expo 58]] | prevunhocity = [[Brussels]] | nextunho = [[Century 21 Exposition]] | nextunhocity =[[Seattle]] | simuni = | simspe = | simhor = | simoth = | website = }}''' '''Floriade 1960''' was a horticultural exhibition and [[garden festival]] held in [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]] which took place from 25 March to 25 September 1960 in Het Park near the [[Meuse (river)|Meuse River]]. It was the first edition of the [[Floriade (Netherlands)|Floriade]] to be organised under the auspices of the Association of International Horticultural Producers ([[AIPH]]) and also the first international [[horticultural exposition]] to be recognised by the [[Bureau International des Expositions]] .
To mark the occasion of the Floriade, the [[Euromast]] was built and inaugurated. The tower was 107 meters high, making it the tallest structure in the city. The tower's height was increased after the end of the Floriade.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euromast.nl/en/about-the-euromast/history|accessdate=4 June 2014|title=History - Euromast}}</ref>
