{{unreferenced|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox single | Name = Pokušaj | Artist = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | Cover = | Released = 2008 | Format = [[CD]] | Recorded = 2008 | Genre = [[Alternative rock]] | Length = | Writer = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | Producer = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | Last single = | This single = | Next single = |Misc = {{Infobox song contest entry | embed=yes | song = {{flagicon|Bosnia and Herzegovina}} "Pokušaj" | image = [[file:ESC 2008 - Bosnia & Herzegovina - Laka, 1st semifinal.jpg|250px]] | caption = | year = 2008 | country = Bosnia and Herzegovina | artist = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | as = Laka | with = [[Mirela Laković]] | language = Bosnian | languages = | composer = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | lyricist = [[Elvir Laković Laka]] | conductor = | place = 10th | points = 110 | place_semi = 9th | points_semi = 72 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?2008ba Lyrics] | clip = [http://www.eurovision.tv/mediaplayer/2008/video/bih.html Video Clip] | prev = Rijeka bez imena | prev_link = Rijeka bez imena | next = Bistra voda | next_link = Bistra voda }}}} '''"Pokušaj"''' (Try), is a song by the Bosnian singer [[Elvir Laković Laka]]. "Pokušaj" is an [[alternative rock]]-style song and was composed and written by Laka, who is a popular alternative rock singer from Bosnia and Herzegovina.
He was internally selected by the Bosnian National broadcaster BHT to represent [[Bosnia and Herzegovina in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. Laka was chosen among many other entries to represent Bosnia and, therefore, the [[Bosnian language|Bosnian]] version represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the [[2008 Eurovision Song Contest]] in Belgrade. On 20 May 2008, the song competed in the first semi-final of Eurovision, and won a place in the final on 24 May, where it was the 6th song performed out of 25. The song finished 10th out of 25, receiving 110 points. Laka performed the song with his younger sister Mirela along with four backing singers dressed as brides.
The song was succeeded as [[Bosnia and Herzegovina in the Eurovision Song Contest|Bosnian representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009 contest]] by [[Regina (Bosnia and Herzegovina band)|Regina]] with "[[Bistra voda]]".
