{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Santiago de Cabo Verde |latin = Dioecesis Sancti Iacobi Capitis Viridis |country = Cape Verde |metropolitan = ''Immediately subject to the Holy See'' |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = [[Pro-Cathedral of Our Lady of Grace, Praia|Pró-catedral Nossa Senhora da Graça]], [[Praia]] |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 1,793 |population = 318,317 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 292,488 |catholics_percent= 91.9 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Arlindo Gomes Furtado]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= |website = {{url|http://diocesesantiago.org}} | coordinates = {{coord|14.9173|N|23.5086|W|source:wikidata|display=it}} }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Santiago de Cabo Verde''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Sancti Iacobi Capitis Viridis}}) is a [[diocese]] of the [[Catholic Church]] in [[Cape Verde]]. It covers the islands of [[Maio, Cape Verde|Maio]], [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]], [[Fogo, Cape Verde|Fogo]], and [[Brava, Cape Verde|Brava]] (the [[Sotavento Islands]]). Its seat is the [[Pro-Cathedral of Our Lady of Grace, Praia|Pró-catedral Nossa Senhora da Graça]] in [[Praia]], Santiago.<ref>[http://diocesesantiago.org/site/index.php/diocese/dados-gerais Dados gerais], Diocese de Santiago de Cabo Verde</ref>
==History== The Diocese of Santiago de Cabo Verde was created on January 31, 1533 as a [[Suffragan diocese|suffragan]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Funchal|Archdiocese of Funchal]] (Azores, Portugal) by [[Pope Clement VII]]. Its seat was [[Cidade Velha|Ribeira Grande]], on Santiago.<ref name=hist>[http://diocesesantiago.org/site/index.php/diocese/historia História], Diocese de Santiago de Cabo Verde</ref> Bishop [[Francisco de la Cruz]] started construction of a cathedral in Ribeira Grande in 1556. Ribeira Grande went into decline in the 18th century, and the seat was moved to [[Ribeira Brava, Cape Verde|Ribeira Brava]] on São Nicolau in 1786, where it stayed until 1943. A seminary and an episcopal palace were built there.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.portaldoconhecimento.gov.cv/bitstream/10961/4125/1/IRTUR2_RBSN_Actual.pdf Inventário dos recursos turísticos do município de Ribeira Brava de São Nicolau], Direcção Geral do Turismo, p. 28-29</ref>
Until September 4, 1940 the diocese covered not only the Cape Verde islands, but also [[Portuguese Guinea]] on the African mainland. Portuguese Guinea became a [[Mission sui iuris|Mission ''sui iuris'']], the later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Bissau]]. Since November 2003 the (northern) [[Barlavento Islands]] form the separate [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mindelo]], and the Diocese of Santiago de Cabo Verde only covers the (southern) Sotavento Islands.<ref name=gcath>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/ztia4.htm Diocese of Santiago de Cabo Verde], GCatholic.org</ref>
==Bishops==
