{{distinguish|Romania}} {{other uses2|Romanija}} {{Infobox mountain | name = Romanija | other_name = | photo = Romanija Landscape.JPG | photo_size = 200 | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Landscape in the Romanija mountain | elevation = | elevation_m = 1652 | elevation_ft = | elevation_ref = | prominence = | prominence_m = | prominence_ft = | prominence_ref = | listing = | range = [[Dinaric Alps]] | parent_peak = | location = [[Republika Srpska]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | map = Bosnia and Herzegovina | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Romanija | map_relief = | map_size = | label = | label_position = | coordinates = {{coord|43|51|36|N|18|40|12|E}} | region_code = | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | volcanic_arc/belt = | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Romanija''' is a mountain, [[karst]] [[plateau]], and geographical region in eastern [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], including numerous villages and towns, such as [[Pale, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Pale]], [[Sokolac]], and [[Han Pijesak]]. Its highest point is Veliki Lupoglav (1,652 m).{{Citation needed|date=November 2014}}
A [[Association football|football]] club from the neighbouring town of [[Pale, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Pale]] bears its name, FK Romanija.
