{{Infobox Airline |airline = Sky Srpska |logo = |logo_size = 200px |IATA = - |ICAO = - |callsign = - |parent = |founded = 2007 |ceased = 2011 |headquarters = [[Banja Luka]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] |key_people = |hubs = [[Banja Luka International Airport]] |focus cities = |frequent_flyer = |lounge = |alliance = |fleet_size = 0 |destinations = 0 |website = {{URL|http://www.skysrpska.aero/}} }}
'''Sky Srpska''' was a planned [[airline]] in the [[Republika Srpska|Republic of Srpska]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. The airline was a public enterprise owned by the [[Government of Republika Srpska|entity government]] and had its hub at the [[Banja Luka International Airport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vladars.net/cr/novosti.php?c=novost&id=3145|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927212240/http://www.vladars.net/cr/novosti.php?c=novost&id=3145|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2007-09-27|author=Government of Republika Srpska|script-title=sr:Одржана 11. сједница Владе Републике Српске|authorlink=Politics of Republika Srpska|accessdate=2007-02-12|date=2007-02-08|language=Serbian}} </ref> The airline launched international services in July 2010 after signing a cooperation agreement with [[Adria Airways]],<ref>[http://www.airlineupdate.com/content_public/airlines/airline_profiles/airlines_bosnia/skysrpska.htm Sky Srpska] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113232952/http://www.airlineupdate.com/content_public/airlines/airline_profiles/airlines_bosnia/skysrpska.htm |date=2013-11-13 }} at airlineupdate.com, retrieved 13-11-2013</ref> selling seats for flights from Banja Luka to Ljubljana. The Republic of Srpska government delayed the launch of the airline on several occasions, but ultimately decided to end its support in 2012 due to the airlines lack of funds to lease an aircraft.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ch-aviation.ch/airlinepage.php?code1=SPP|title=Sky Srpska|publisher=ch-aviation|accessdate=2007-05-05}}</ref>
